---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research"
  description="Research of Junming Wen, PhD researcher at the University of Glasgow."
>
  <div class="px-6 py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto" style="max-width: var(--content-width);">

      <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent">Research</p>
      <h1 class="mb-8 font-serif text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
        Research
      </h1>

      <!-- ── PhD Project ─────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">PhD Research</h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-slate-400">University of Glasgow &nbsp;·&nbsp; 2025 – Present</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
          My PhD research focuses on the green and sustainable transformation of manufacturing supply chains in the context of digital technology adoption. With increasing pressure on manufacturing firms to improve their environmental and sustainability performance, the integration of big data and artificial intelligence into supply chain operations has become a key area of interest. My research examines the relationship between digital technology adoption and supply chain sustainability in manufacturing, with the goal of providing insights that are useful for both academic understanding and practical decision-making.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
          The research sits at the crossroads of operations management, sustainability, and technology management, drawing on multiple research perspectives to address questions that are relevant to firms operating in complex and data-rich environments. Rather than focusing on any single industry or region, the work aims to offer findings that are broadly applicable to manufacturing contexts where sustainability pressures and digital capabilities are both present.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-slate-200" />

      <!-- ── Research Experience ─────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="mb-5 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Research Experience</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">

          <!-- CRDB Slotting Strategy -->
          <article class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
            <div class="mb-3 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400">
                Dec 2022 – May 2023
              </span>
              <span class="rounded-full bg-accent-subtle px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-accent">
                Completed
              </span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
              Category and Request Date-Based (CRDB) Slotting Strategy
            </h3>
            <p class="mb-3 text-sm text-slate-400">
              National University of Singapore &amp; Bolloré Logistics &nbsp;·&nbsp; Supervisor: Assoc. Prof. Bandi Chaithanya
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
              Developed a slotting model and strategy for small-scale warehouses in collaboration with Bolloré Logistics (Asia-Pacific hub, Singapore), improving operational efficiency by 31.32%. Awarded Best Research Paper (A+).
            </p>
          </article>

        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
